Analysis of the Target Structure
--------------------------------

1) Overall Count & Layers

•  The tower at left uses a total of 10 blocks arranged in (approximately) five layers from bottom to top:

   Layer 1 (bottom):
   – 1 yellow rectangular block

   Layer 2:
   – 2 orange cylinders standing on the yellow block

   Layer 3:
   – 1 yellow rectangular block bridging across the top of the two cylinders

   Layer 4:
   – 2 blue cubes side by side
   – 1 red arch block behind the cubes on the same level

   Layer 5 (top):
   – 1 red cube resting on top of the arch
   – 2 orange wedge blocks forming a pitched roof

•  The separate smaller structure on the right uses 3 blocks in a single layer:
   – 1 blue cube in the center
   – 2 orange wedges (one on each side)

2) Which Dictionary Blocks Match?
---------------------------------

From the provided block dictionary, the following pieces (by index) match exactly in shape/color/orientation (no rotations allowed other than those shown):

• Yellow rectangular blocks (for tower’s bottom and bridging piece):  #6  
  (use two of these)

• Orange cylinders: #9  
  (use two of these)

• Blue cubes: #4  
  – two cubes for the tower  
  – one more cube for the small side‐structure  
  (total three #4 cubes)

• Red arch (with curved opening on the underside): #1  
  (one needed)

• Red cube (the small red block that sits on top of the arch): #5  
  (one needed)

• Orange wedges (for the tower’s roof): #13 and #16  
  – one pair (#13 + #16) for the top roof of the tower  

• Orange wedges (for the small side structure): #13 and #16 again  
  – another pair (#13 + #16) flanking the blue cube on the ground  

Hence in total you will use:
– 2 × #6  
– 2 × #9  
– 3 × #4  
– 1 × #1  
– 1 × #5  
– 2 × #13  
– 2 × #16  

3) Assembly Order
-----------------

Below is a suggested step‐by‐step sequence.  Remember that the same index may appear multiple times if more than one identical piece is needed.

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 6   (place first yellow rectangular block as the tower’s base)  
  Step2:  Move block with index 9   (place first orange cylinder on the base)  
  Step3:  Move block with index 9   (place second orange cylinder on the base)  
  Step4:  Move block with index 6   (place second yellow rectangular block bridging over the two cylinders)  
  Step5:  Move block with index 4   (place first blue cube on top)  
  Step6:  Move block with index 4   (place second blue cube on top)  
  Step7:  Move block with index 1   (place the red arch behind/over the two blue cubes)  
  Step8:  Move block with index 5   (place the red cube on top of the arch)  
  Step9:  Move block with index 13  (place left orange wedge for the roof)  
  Step10: Move block with index 16  (place right orange wedge for the roof)  

  -- Now assemble the smaller side structure --

  Step11: Move block with index 13  (place left orange wedge on the ground)  
  Step12: Move block with index 4   (place the blue cube between the wedges)  
  Step13: Move block with index 16  (place right orange wedge on the ground)  
}

Following these steps and using the indicated block indices will reproduce the target arrangement exactly as shown.
